Package org.svvrl.goal.core.comp.ramsey

Class ProfileAutomaton

java.lang.Object
org.svvrl.goal.core.AbstractEditable
org.svvrl.goal.core.aut.Automaton
org.svvrl.goal.core.aut.fsa.FSA
org.svvrl.goal.core.comp.ramsey.ProfileAutomaton
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.beans.PropertyChangeListener, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.EventListener, Editable
public class ProfileAutomaton
extends FSA
This class provides an implementation of the Ã in [A. Prasad Sistla, Moshe Y. Vardi, and Pierre Wolper. The complementation problem for Buchi automata with applications to temporal logic. Theoretical Computer Science, 49:217-237, 1987]. This automaton has an empty classic acceptance condition. Each state of this automaton has a corresponding profile. Any change on this automaton may break the relation between profiles and states.
Author:
Ming-Hsien Tsai
